caption: Very tiny place. This little pizza spot is a gem. It is a hole in the wall.  My kid and I like it, a lot. The owner is friendly and gives off this good energy. He looks like he loves what he does. You know what they say about food prepared with love; it is great!  Even though the place is tiny, we always choose to stay and eat here. Pizza should not go into a box and carried out. That is my opinion.  The pizza is just right. Not too thin or thick. Just the right amount of cheese and sauce. It is not like those soft, sloppy slices that you get at some places. I eat the crust here; I rarely eat the crust.  We usually get two plain cheese slices, and I will get one with pineapples, mushrooms, and black olives.  If you are in the area and, want to eat delicious pizza. Come here; it will not disappoint.  -Toppins are 0.50 cents each. -They take cash and credit cards.
